<div id="pf5a" class="pf w0 h3" data-page-no="5a"><div class="pc pc5a w0 h3"><div class="t m842 x5 h38 ya58 ff7 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4sisfifftg,.. </div><div class="t m843 x6f h39 y4d6 ff5 fs20 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath Afternoon </div><div class="t m7b0 x6f h6 y3b9 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Lesson 13 </div><div class="t m52 x84 h6 ya59 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">î˜‰</div><div class="t m844 x2b h6 y3b9 ff3 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">September 19-25 </div><div class="t m297 x75 h3a ya5a ff3 fs21 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Rebirth Is Renewal </div><div class="t m768 x6f h13 y233 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">READ FOR THIS WEEK&apos;S STUDY: Titus 3. </div><div class="t m76a x6b h13 ya5b ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEMORY TEXT: &quot;Not by works of righteousness which </div><div class="t m845 x6b h13 ya5c ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">we have done, but according to his mercy he saved us, by </div><div class="t m2f0 x6b h13 ya5d ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the washing of regeneration, and renewing of the Holy </div><div class="t m5d4 x6b h13 ya5e ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ghost&quot; (Titus 3:5). </div><div class="t m31c x5b h13 y9e8 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">KEY THOUGHT: </div><div class="t m846 x1a h11 y23b ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Spiritual rebirth by faith and daily living </div><div class="t m847 x6f h11 y23c ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by faith in Jesus Christ result in the power to follow the </div><div class="t m14f x6f h11 y9a5 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">inspired practical counsel given by Paul. </div><div class="t m29 x5b h13 y3f7 ff3 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">PAUL CONCLUDES HIS INSTRUCTION TO TITUS. </div><div class="t m848 x14 h11 y23f ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In </div><div class="t m61c x6f h11 y3f8 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the concluding chapter of his Epistle to Titus, Paul reempha-</div><div class="t m50c x6f h11 ya5f ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sizes the importance of exemplary living. In his relationships </div><div class="t m849 x6f h11 y3fa ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with secular authorities the Christian should not only be above </div><div class="t m84a x6f h11 y9ef ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reproach, but should &quot;be ready to do whatever is good&quot; (verse </div><div class="t m314 x6f h11 y9f1 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1, NIV). </div><div class="t m84b x5b h11 y245 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">When we were living in habitual sin, we were ruled by our </div><div class="t m84c x6f h11 y9f3 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">passions and in constant conflict with our fellow human be-</div><div class="t m113 x6f h11 y9f4 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ings. Then came rebirth and renewal by the inner saving work </div><div class="t m84d x6f h11 y9f5 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of the Holy Spirit. The power to live as God instructs is </div><div class="t m13a x6f h11 ya60 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">provided by the saving grace of Christ bestowed upon us by </div><div class="t m555 x6f h11 y9f7 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Holy Spirit. Salvation through Christ not only fits us for </div><div class="t m27f x6f h11 ya61 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">worthy citizenship on earth, it makes us &quot;heirs according to </div><div class="t m223 x6f h11 y9f8 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the hope of eternal life&quot; (verse 7). </div><div class="t m84e x5b h11 y96c ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Titus 3 provides one of Scripture&apos;s clearest statements of </div><div class="t m84f x6f h11 y96d ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">salvation by grace resulting in good works. </div><div class="t m1f2 x6f h11 ya62 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">90 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
